<dl id="n54135g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54135g">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54135g"> 135(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cornelian</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In clothing and adornment there can be no question that our Viking forefathers had attained a high standard of luxury. Any visitor to the great national museums at Copenhagen, Stockholm or Christiania must be impressed by the wealth of personal ornaments displayed before him: magnificent brooches of silver and bronze, arm-rings and neck-rings of gold and silver, large beads of silver, glass, rock-crystal, amber and <mark>cornelian</mark>. <small> Allen Mawers, <a name="VIK2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#VIK2"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a> (1913) 104</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
